anking system, he assesses the significance of cooperation within both bilateral and multilateral accords, including the Israeli-Palestinian Interim Accords of 1993–1995, the Lesotho Highlands Water Treaty of 1986, and the 1994 Convention on Cooperation for the Protection and Sustainable Use of the River Danube. Gordon identifies central factors and stakeholders that are necessary for mitigating the risk of conflict and presents a template for understanding how state behavior can manage and sustain regional water resources.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEnvironmental policyxInternational cooperation. 0aFresh waterxGovernment policyxInternational cooperation. 0aWater resources developmentxInternational cooperation. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Politics. 4aEnvironmental Studies : International Environmental Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147734240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477342/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles